headline: AI Has Pushed the Stock Market to Record Highs. Why the Economy Could Drag It Down.
summary: Investors are getting mixed messages on health of the U.S. economy, leaving stocks in limbo ahead of next week’s Federal Reserve rate decision.  After being powered by the artificial-intelligence trade all year, stocks don’t seem to know where to head this month—traditionally one of the market’s strongest—thanks to data showing solid gains in some corners of the world’s biggest economy, and ongoing weakness in others.  Lower Fed interest rates would almost surely support market valuations over the months ahead.

headline: Heard on the Street Wednesday Recap: Betting on Cuts
summary: The Dow industrials added 0.9% and the Nasdaq composite gained 0.2%.  New data from ADP showed the private sector shed 32,000 jobs in November.  The "modest fall" should be enough to persuade Federal Reserve policymakers to vote for another rate cut next week, said Stephen Brown of Capital Economics.

headline: Clients Want the Everything-Store Experience
summary: The financial industry and clients have been trying to replicate that one-stop shopping experience for portfolios.  Advised households tend to use multiple shops, having a full service account with their wealth manager, as well as a self-directed brokerage account at another firm.  More and more, clients are looking to consolidate their assets and services under one roof, which can be quite a tall task for firms.

headline: Symbotic Stock Tanks 15%. Why Walmart’s Partner Is Falling.
summary: Symbotic  stock plummeted on Thursday after the warehouse robotics company announced a public offering of 10 million shares of common stock.  Symbotic  which is a key strategic partner of  Walmart  is offering 6.5 million shares in a primary offering and SVF Sponsor III, an affiliate of  SoftBank Group  is selling 3.5 million shares, Symbotic said in a statement dated Wednesday afternoon.

headline: ICSC Announces John Peter (JP) Suarez as ICSC Chairman and Conor Flynn as ICSC Vice Chairman for 2026
summary: NEW YORK, December 04, 2025--ICSC announced today that the organization’s Board of Trustees elected John Peter (JP) Suarez, Former Walmart International Regional CEO, Executive Vice President and Chief Administration Officer, to serve as ICSC’s Chairman and Conor Flynn, Kimco Realty CEO, to serve as Vice Chairman for the 2026 term. JP succeeds Angele Robinson-Gaylord, SVP, Store Development Americas, Starbucks Coffee Company, as ICSC’s 65th Chairman.
